\begin_layout Standard
The objective of this work is to propose a novel method of detecting anomalies
 on a time series in an online fashion.
 The presented method is based on an approach to time series analysis called
 Merge Growing Neural Gas (MGNG).
 As we will show, we use MGNG in a way such that it allows us to detect
 anomalies in (almost) real time, on multidimensional spaces, making no
 assumptions about the data, and with time performance dependent only on
 the parameters and input dimensionality, but 
\series bold
independent
\series default
 of the number of data points.
\end_layout

